00:00:41.960 --> 00:00:48.460
To be best prepared to replace the Power Supply
Unit (PSU) Board inside of your TV, you will

00:00:48.460 --> 00:00:50.920
need the following materials:
A pair of latex gloves.

00:00:50.920 --> 00:00:53.570
Your ShopJimmy.com replacement Power Supply
Unit (PSU) Board.

00:00:53.570 --> 00:00:55.720
A pair of needle-nose pliers.

00:00:55.720 --> 00:00:57.570
Both a flat-head and phillips screwdriver.

00:00:57.570 --> 00:01:01.480
And a cup to hold all screws, clips, and any
other small items.

00:01:01.480 --> 00:01:05.350
So let's get to it, shall we?

00:01:05.350 --> 00:01:09.880
Locate your TVs identification sticker and
take note of the brand name, model number,

00:01:09.880 --> 00:01:14.740
serial number, and model code if present.

00:01:14.740 --> 00:01:18.530
Unscrew and remove the back cover.

00:01:18.530 --> 00:01:22.780
The power supply unit takes in and distributes
power throughout the TV.

00:01:22.780 --> 00:01:26.340
This board is connected to the power cord
or the A/C adapter.

00:01:26.340 --> 00:01:31.840
This power supply is located at the center
of the chassis.

00:01:31.840 --> 00:01:39.979
Carefully unplug all wires by hand.

00:01:39.979 --> 00:01:44.799
Unlock the wire connectors by squeezing the
tab or tabs and gently remove the wires.

00:01:44.799 --> 00:01:51.259
Be sure to keep a firm grip with both hands.

00:01:51.259 --> 00:01:57.520
Unscrew and gently remove the bad Power Supply
Unit (PSU) Board from the chassis.

00:01:57.520 --> 00:02:02.670
Search your TV model number on http://www.shopjimmy.com/
to find a compatible replacement.

00:02:02.670 --> 00:02:07.659
Filter your search results by the appropriate
part type.

00:02:07.659 --> 00:02:10.979
Click on the search results to view important
product specifications.

00:02:10.979 --> 00:02:15.199
Verify that your original board matches all
requirements noted in the product description

00:02:15.199 --> 00:02:28.230
prior to purchase.

00:02:28.230 --> 00:02:35.160
Insert all screws to secure your ShopJimmy
new Power Supply Unit (PSU) Board to the chassis.

00:02:35.160 --> 00:02:43.290
Reconnect all cables.

00:02:43.290 --> 00:02:47.970
Return the back cover to its original position
and secure all screws.

00:02:47.970 --> 00:02:51.340
This ShopJimmy replacement Power Supply Unit
(PSU) Board does not require any manual configurations

00:02:51.340 --> 00:02:53.590
in order to function.

00:02:53.590 --> 00:02:56.799
Simply plug in and power on and your TV will
function as if new!

